how are we able to live together

01:37:07.640 --> 01:37:13.500 position:56%
as a multi-cultural, multi-religious
entity, because the processes

01:37:13.500 --> 01:37:17.370
of globalization are
creating so much turmoil

01:37:17.370 --> 01:37:20.270
through all sorts of processes.

01:37:20.270 --> 01:37:23.620
And this idea will
relate to what I'm going

01:37:23.620 --> 01:37:26.740 position:56%
to be sharing with you this morning.

01:37:26.740 --> 01:37:29.780
My title for those of
you who looked at this --

01:37:29.780 --> 01:37:35.910
the proceedings for this morning
will note is "A New Andaluca?"

01:37:35.910 --> 01:37:41.610
You will also note I have put a
question mark after the title.

01:37:41.610 --> 01:37:44.110
For me, Andalucia symbolizes
something

01:37:44.110 --> 01:37:47.230
in our history and world history.

01:37:47.230 --> 01:37:53.930
It symbolizes a time almost a
thousand years ago when Jews,

01:37:53.930 --> 01:38:00.070
Christians, and Muslims were able
to live together in great harmony.

01:38:00.070 --> 01:38:04.730
This wasn't just an ideal
construct, a theory.

01:38:04.730 --> 01:38:06.280
But it created something.

01:38:06.280 --> 01:38:12.830
If you look at the literature,
the art, the level of thought

01:38:12.830 --> 01:38:15.970 position:56%
at that time, you will be astounded.

01:38:15.970 --> 01:38:18.810
Some of the greatest
writers and thinkers come

01:38:18.810 --> 01:38:21.860
from that era in world history.

01:38:21.860 --> 01:38:23.460
Above all, it was a society

01:38:23.460 --> 01:38:26.970
where people were able
to talk, talk freely.

01:38:26.970 --> 01:38:28.850
There was open debate.

01:38:28.850 --> 01:38:32.660
So Jews, Muslims, Christians,
talked to each other.

01:38:32.660 --> 01:38:37.050
It was through this civilization
that Europe and the West learned

01:38:37.050 --> 01:38:41.960
of its own history and its
own foundations, the Greeks.

01:38:41.960 --> 01:38:47.010 position:56%
If there'd been no Muslims in Spain
perhaps the Renaissance may not even

01:38:47.010 --> 01:38:48.460
have taken place.

01:38:48.460 --> 01:38:56.940
And I came across several great
scholars, American scholars,

01:38:56.940 --> 01:39:02.860
scholars like Professor Tamara
Sun, Professor John Esposito,

01:39:02.860 --> 01:39:07.500
Professor Dinah Eck, who were
exploring this idea of America

01:39:07.500 --> 01:39:12.480
as a New Andalusia,
America as a society

01:39:12.480 --> 01:39:17.430
which was relatively comparatively
but very advanced in terms

01:39:17.430 --> 01:39:20.250
of peoples and cultures
living together.

01:39:20.250 --> 01:39:25.110
There was a genuine feeling
of welcome to the immigrant

01:39:25.110 --> 01:39:27.570
because America essentially
is a society

01:39:27.570 --> 01:39:30.380
of immigrants welcoming
other immigrants.

01:39:30.380 --> 01:39:35.060
And that gave it a certain flavor
and a character in America.

01:39:35.060 --> 01:39:38.320
I discussed this with a colleague
of mine at Princeton University

01:39:38.320 --> 01:39:43.640
in making a comparison between
European experiences with Islam

01:39:43.640 --> 01:39:45.570
and American experiences.

01:39:45.570 --> 01:39:49.250
And he told me, a very wise
Professor of Anthropology

01:39:49.250 --> 01:39:51.800
who studied the Muslim world,
he said the difference is

01:39:51.800 --> 01:39:55.280
that in America the door's open.

01:39:55.280 --> 01:39:56.580
There is no restriction.

01:39:56.580 --> 01:39:58.050
You want to make a mosque,
go and make a mosque.

01:39:58.050 --> 01:40:00.810
You want to make an Islamic
center, go and make it.

01:40:00.810 --> 01:40:02.390
Of course, that is on one level.

01:40:02.390 --> 01:40:07.040
We know that on another level
there are three distinct streams

01:40:07.040 --> 01:40:08.890
in the American Muslim community --

01:40:08.890 --> 01:40:11.240
the Afro-American stream
of which we've heard

01:40:11.240 --> 01:40:14.930
with such eloquence this
morning, the Arab stream

01:40:14.930 --> 01:40:17.360
from the Middle East,
and then the Asian stream

01:40:17.360 --> 01:40:19.590
which came more recently.

01:40:19.590 --> 01:40:22.680
We also know that these
three streams run parallel,

01:40:22.680 --> 01:40:27.060
sometimes they fuse, sometimes
they maintain their own identity.

01:40:27.060 --> 01:40:30.750
We also know that there are
individuals in the first stream,

01:40:30.750 --> 01:40:32.810
individuals who are towering,

01:40:32.810 --> 01:40:36.530
who are in a sense gigantic
figures acting as bridges

01:40:36.530 --> 01:40:39.190
between not only the
three streams but outside.

01:40:39.190 --> 01:40:42.580
And I refer to figures like
Malcolm X and Muhammad [inaudible]

01:40:42.580 --> 01:40:44.540
as much an Afro-American stars.

01:40:44.540 --> 01:40:45.840
He is an American stars.

01:40:45.840 --> 01:40:47.700
He's much a Muslim star.

01:40:47.700 --> 01:40:49.750
So for someone in Pakistan,
my country,

01:40:49.750 --> 01:40:52.400
he'd be a complete superstar.

01:40:52.400 --> 01:40:56.600
Now, September 11 and
Osama bin Laden --

01:40:56.600 --> 01:41:00.520
Osama bin Laden challenges
many things on September 11.

01:41:00.520 --> 01:41:02.640
And I believe one of the great,

01:41:02.640 --> 01:41:09.280
great ideas that he challenges
is the idea of the New Andalusia.

01:41:09.280 --> 01:41:10.900
He does challenge that.

01:41:10.900 --> 01:41:14.420
And as a result of this
we have immediately

01:41:14.420 --> 01:41:17.790
after September 11 three
things happening --

01:41:17.790 --> 01:41:22.030
the levels of ignorance about
Islam, the levels of understanding

01:41:22.030 --> 01:41:26.420
about Islam, and the levels
of hatred against Islam.

01:41:26.420 --> 01:41:29.000
These three things become
immediately apparent

01:41:29.000 --> 01:41:31.020
after September 11.

01:41:31.020 --> 01:41:32.320
And you have so many cases.

01:41:32.320 --> 01:41:34.710
You have men with beards
wearing a turban.

01:41:34.710 --> 01:41:38.160
Sometime Sikhs, not even
Muslim, being attacked.

01:41:38.160 --> 01:41:41.800
You have women wearing the hijab
being abused or humiliated,

01:41:41.800 --> 01:41:44.160
or forced to take their hijab off.

01:41:44.160 --> 01:41:47.010
And we suddenly have
a great challenge

01:41:47.010 --> 01:41:50.380
to the idea of a New Andalusia.

01:41:50.380 --> 01:41:52.290
At the same time, with
this great challenge,

01:41:52.290 --> 01:41:57.450
we also have a new opportunity
because there is a genuine interest

01:41:57.450 --> 01:41:59.700
in Islam after September 11.

01:41:59.700 --> 01:42:01.640
People want to know about Islam.

01:42:01.640 --> 01:42:04.100
So matched with the great ignorance

01:42:04.100 --> 01:42:06.780
on one hand there is
a great interest.

01:42:06.780 --> 01:42:09.670
And the ignorance cuts
across at all levels.

01:42:09.670 --> 01:42:14.780
Sometimes I aghast at the media
and the experts on the media.

01:42:14.780 --> 01:42:19.710
Recently I heard a commentary
on the prisoners in Cuba,

01:42:19.710 --> 01:42:23.370
and one of the experts was
explaining why the beards

01:42:23.370 --> 01:42:25.010
of these prisoners were shaved.

01:42:25.010 --> 01:42:27.190
And the expert was
saying they were shaved

01:42:27.190 --> 01:42:29.240
so that they could become purer.

01:42:29.240 --> 01:42:31.460
It was a purification process.

01:42:31.460 --> 01:42:32.760
And I was aghast.

01:42:32.760 --> 01:42:36.490
How do you respond to something
which is this level of ignorance?

01:42:36.490 --> 01:42:40.750 position:56%
And, really, in a sense that is what
we are up against, the challenges

01:42:40.750 --> 01:42:43.040
of trying to create understanding

01:42:43.040 --> 01:42:46.530
and mutual dialog between
the communities.

01:42:46.530 --> 01:42:49.880
So our work as scholars
interested in Islam

01:42:49.880 --> 01:42:52.680
in America is really cut out.

01:42:52.680 --> 01:42:57.630
The great challenge today is how
to explain Islam in an environment

01:42:57.630 --> 01:43:03.920
which is, A, volatile,
B, often hostile, and C,

01:43:03.920 --> 01:43:09.360
accumulation of so many years
and years and years of prejudice,

01:43:09.360 --> 01:43:12.310
history, and negative images.

01:43:12.310 --> 01:43:15.180
We've heard the negative images
that have come from the media,

01:43:15.180 --> 01:43:18.840
particularly Hollywood and the
films, so I won't go into that.

01:43:18.840 --> 01:43:23.740
So Muslims are in a
sense in the dark.

01:43:23.740 --> 01:43:28.330
Whether people accept that or do
not accept it, anyone I ever name

01:43:28.330 --> 01:43:30.660
which ends with Ahmed or Amed.

01:43:30.660 --> 01:43:34.870
Try going to a check-in counter at
an airline with the name like that.

01:43:34.870 --> 01:43:36.650
You're going to be looked
over very carefully.

01:43:36.650 --> 01:43:38.490
You're going to be
asked to step aside.

01:43:38.490 --> 01:43:43.240
You've suddenly become aware that
whatever you are, whoever you are,

01:43:43.240 --> 01:43:47.920 position:56%
you are suddenly representative of
the Islamic civilization as a whole.

01:43:47.920 --> 01:43:49.220
And why not?

01:43:49.220 --> 01:43:50.520
Just look at what's happening.

01:43:50.520 --> 01:43:51.820
Look at the media.

01:43:51.820 --> 01:43:55.600
Constantly Islam or
Muslims are in the news.

01:43:55.600 --> 01:43:59.770
There's a Muslim story
all the time on the media.

01:43:59.770 --> 01:44:02.690
[Inaudible], Muslims;
Philippines [inaudible] Muslims.

01:44:02.690 --> 01:44:03.990
Where are we going next?

01:44:03.990 --> 01:44:06.990
Somalia, Iraq, Iran, Muslim,
Muslim, Muslim, Muslim.

01:44:06.990 --> 01:44:08.530
Captives, all Muslims.

01:44:08.530 --> 01:44:09.830
All captives.

01:44:09.830 --> 01:44:11.180
Johnny Jihad.

01:44:11.180 --> 01:44:14.480
Muslims, Muslims, Muslims
are always in the news.

01:44:14.480 --> 01:44:17.240
So however much we pretend
that we as scholars,

01:44:17.240 --> 01:44:20.220
we live in our own world, we write
our books, we have nothing to do

01:44:20.220 --> 01:44:24.480
with the real world, we
are part of the debate.

01:44:24.480 --> 01:44:29.780
I see all of us facing
several crises.

01:44:29.780 --> 01:44:35.150
The first crisis, for of these
crises is the crisis of identity.

01:44:35.150 --> 01:44:38.110
I believe that this has
thrown open the issue

01:44:38.110 --> 01:44:40.910
of identity in Muslim society.

01:44:40.910 --> 01:44:42.210
Are we Arabs?

01:44:42.210 --> 01:44:43.510
Are we Pakistanis?

01:44:43.510 --> 01:44:44.810
Are we American Muslims?

01:44:44.810 --> 01:44:48.460 position:56%
Are we part of the world [inaudible]
or are we only American Muslims,

01:44:48.460 --> 01:44:50.930
defined politically
and geographically

01:44:50.930 --> 01:44:52.580
by the borders around America?

01:44:52.580 --> 01:44:54.910
Number one, identity.

01:44:54.910 --> 01:44:57.280
Number two, theology.

01:44:57.280 --> 01:45:00.680
The debate about Islamic self.

01:45:00.680 --> 01:45:02.670
Does the Koran encourage violence?

01:45:02.670 --> 01:45:04.580
I'm asked that all the time.

01:45:04.580 --> 01:45:06.750
And I'm sure other Muslims
are asked that all the time.

01:45:06.750 --> 01:45:08.550
We need answers.

01:45:08.550 --> 01:45:11.750 position:56%
It is not good enough for me to say,
well, you must know we are peaceful,

01:45:11.750 --> 01:45:13.050
we love you, we love America.

01:45:13.050 --> 01:45:14.630
Islam is a peaceful religion.

01:45:14.630 --> 01:45:19.350
That has been the Muslim
response and that just will not do

01:45:19.350 --> 01:45:20.650
because no one is buying that.

01:45:20.650 --> 01:45:23.340
After you kill 5000
people or 4000 people,

01:45:23.340 --> 01:45:26.240
you blow up the [inaudible] you
can't simply say there is no

01:45:26.240 --> 01:45:27.540
violence [inaudible] there.

01:45:27.540 --> 01:45:29.180
We need explanations.

01:45:29.180 --> 01:45:31.040
We don't need cliches.

01:45:31.040 --> 01:45:32.340
So theology.

01:45:32.340 --> 01:45:34.230
We need the theologians
and the scholars

01:45:34.230 --> 01:45:38.260
to be giving us the answers rooted
in their knowledge of the Koran

01:45:38.260 --> 01:45:41.080
and the Hadis and Islamic history.

01:45:41.080 --> 01:45:43.290
The questions people asking.

01:45:43.290 --> 01:45:45.900
Three, Muslim leadership.

01:45:45.900 --> 01:45:49.900 position:56%
I believe there's a crisis of Muslim
leadership in America right now.

01:45:49.900 --> 01:45:52.280
Who are the Muslim leaders?

01:45:52.280 --> 01:45:55.890
I simply hear people in the
media saying Islam is peaceful,

01:45:55.890 --> 01:45:57.490
Islam is peaceful.

01:45:57.490 --> 01:45:59.970
This chant, this incantentiation
[assumed spelling]

01:45:59.970 --> 01:46:01.270
which doesn't mean anything.

01:46:01.270 --> 01:46:03.580
What does this mean Islam
is a peaceful religion?

01:46:03.580 --> 01:46:05.190
It doesn't explain anything.

01:46:05.190 --> 01:46:09.050
We need the Muslim leadership
to connect with the community,

01:46:09.050 --> 01:46:11.240
number one, their own
community and, number two,

01:46:11.240 --> 01:46:13.280
with the larger American community.

01:46:13.280 --> 01:46:15.080
That is not happening.

01:46:15.080 --> 01:46:19.140
Number four, education.

01:46:19.140 --> 01:46:25.240 position:56%
Muslim education and larger American
education, where do they meet?

01:46:25.240 --> 01:46:27.110
Where do they divert?

01:46:27.110 --> 01:46:29.720
We hear so much talk
about the madrassa.

01:46:29.720 --> 01:46:32.300
Have we had position
papers on the madrassa?

01:46:32.300 --> 01:46:34.490
Do we know anything
about the madrassa?

01:46:34.490 --> 01:46:36.050
What is the madrassa?

01:46:36.050 --> 01:46:38.030
The madrassa is the
religious system,

01:46:38.030 --> 01:46:42.740 position:56%
the religious education system,
that eventually created the Taliban.

01:46:42.740 --> 01:46:46.690 position:56%
But at the same time the madrassa is
the foundation for Islamic learning

01:46:46.690 --> 01:46:49.470
and has been for the
last thousand years.

01:46:49.470 --> 01:46:51.690
So does that needed information?

01:46:51.690 --> 01:46:54.410
What do we need to do
about the madrassa?

01:46:54.410 --> 01:46:58.640
We also know that there's a
crisis, not only in Muslim society

01:46:58.640 --> 01:47:00.930
in analyzing non-Muslims,

01:47:00.930 --> 01:47:03.910
but in non-Muslims
looking at Muslim society.

01:47:03.910 --> 01:47:07.070
There's also a failure in
non-Muslims studying Muslims

01:47:07.070 --> 01:47:09.010
or commenting on Muslims.

01:47:09.010 --> 01:47:11.990
I see four experts,
all four non-Muslims,

01:47:11.990 --> 01:47:13.930
commenting on Muslim issues.

01:47:13.930 --> 01:47:16.500
And all four having
the same opinion.

01:47:16.500 --> 01:47:19.160
So A will say Islam
is a violent religion.

01:47:19.160 --> 01:47:21.680
B will say yes, it's a
terribly violent religion.

01:47:21.680 --> 01:47:23.890
C will say it's an even
more violent religion.

01:47:23.890 --> 01:47:25.990
And D will agree with this.

01:47:25.990 --> 01:47:27.780
I don't see much debate.

01:47:27.780 --> 01:47:30.070
I don't see much interaction
of ideas.

01:47:30.070 --> 01:47:32.370
And when a Muslim expert
often appears

01:47:32.370 --> 01:47:35.110
in the media he's often
shouted down.

01:47:35.110 --> 01:47:38.450
There's a tendency to
simply dismiss him or her.

01:47:38.450 --> 01:47:42.040 position:56%
So there is a problem of
communication right now in the media

01:47:42.040 --> 01:47:44.520
and we may again say the
media doesn't have an impact.

01:47:44.520 --> 01:47:46.490
It's just the media.

01:47:46.490 --> 01:47:48.820
But I would like to remind you

01:47:48.820 --> 01:47:52.880
that the media determines
how ordinary people think

01:47:52.880 --> 01:47:54.680
in any country.

01:47:54.680 --> 01:47:57.570
And the power of the
media is so great

01:47:57.570 --> 01:48:02.960
that this may damage those people
like me who are talking of dialog

01:48:02.960 --> 01:48:05.500
of civilizations of understanding.

01:48:05.500 --> 01:48:10.300
It is a very frustrating moment to
be a Muslim in America at this time

01:48:10.300 --> 01:48:13.430
because I feel that the
challenge is so great.

01:48:13.430 --> 01:48:16.300
I also know that there are
millions and millions of people

01:48:16.300 --> 01:48:19.280
on both sides, Muslims
and non-Muslims,

01:48:19.280 --> 01:48:25.020 position:56%
who are taking this challenge as an
opportunity to move towards the idea

01:48:25.020 --> 01:48:28.170
of dialog, to try to
create understanding.

01:48:28.170 --> 01:48:31.610
And I would like to
end with the notion,

01:48:31.610 --> 01:48:34.880
