01:49:09.980 --> 01:49:12.560
to say I am different,
my color is different,

01:49:12.560 --> 01:49:15.590
my religion is different,
and yet I have respect.

01:49:15.590 --> 01:49:17.290
I think that is a great ideal.

01:49:17.290 --> 01:49:22.040
And as a Muslim I would
like to share the vision

01:49:22.040 --> 01:49:26.540
that the Holy Prophet in the
seventh century gave of this ideal

01:49:26.540 --> 01:49:31.400
of New Andalusia in the last
great address that he presented

01:49:31.400 --> 01:49:36.240
to humanity in which he said,
"There is no Arab or non-Arab,

01:49:36.240 --> 01:49:38.460
there is no black or
there is no white."

01:49:38.460 --> 01:49:40.300
And this was the seventh century.

01:49:40.300 --> 01:49:44.610
This was a thousand years before
anyone was talking about equality.

01:49:44.610 --> 01:49:48.120
This is the vision that
drives Muslim society.

01:49:48.120 --> 01:49:53.910 position:56%
And I believe at that point it meets
the American ideal of New Andalusia.

01:49:53.910 --> 01:49:55.210
Thank you.

