kinds of learning and network

02:11:39.360 --> 02:11:43.970
that we've just heard
from Professor Diouf.

02:11:43.970 --> 02:11:51.570 position:56%
And what Professor Ahmed emphasized,
the new Andalucia ties back

02:11:51.570 --> 02:11:57.510
to that also because not only was
Andalucia symbolically a society

02:11:57.510 --> 02:12:03.450
of tolerance, but it was a society
of intellectual inclusiveness.

02:12:03.450 --> 02:12:06.740 position:56%
And it was not only the Greek
learning, but the Byzantine learning

02:12:06.740 --> 02:12:13.530
that came through Islam and
eventually not only through Spain,

02:12:13.530 --> 02:12:18.870
but also through Sicily, and
through the North Africa people

02:12:18.870 --> 02:12:21.020
like Ibn Khaldun himself.

02:12:21.020 --> 02:12:27.480
So there is a -- this tradition
of learning, of inclusiveness

02:12:27.480 --> 02:12:33.180
to discovery from the
ancient classical West

02:12:33.180 --> 02:12:40.870 position:56%
and from the Byzantine world of what
is now Turkey in Eastern Orthodoxy.

02:12:40.870 --> 02:12:46.490
All of that is incorporated in
the tradition of Islamic learning.

02:12:46.490 --> 02:12:49.630
And these networks, as has been
suggested several times today,

02:12:49.630 --> 02:12:53.390
these networks were expanded
by sailors, and traders,

02:12:53.390 --> 02:12:57.110
and others all over the world.

02:12:57.110 --> 02:13:04.500
